S(z) = \prod_{i=1}^n (z-z_i)
\frac{1}{S(z)}\frac{d^2S}{dz^2} = \sum_{i=1}^n\frac{1}{z-z_i}\sum_{j\neq i}^n\frac{2}{z_i-z_j}
 \frac{1}{S(z)}\frac{dS}{dz}= \sum_{i=1}^n\frac{1}{z-z_i} 
S(z)
{\frac {1}{ \left( z-z_{{i}} \right)  \left( z-z_{{j}} \right) }}={ \frac {1}{ \left( z_{{i}}-z_{{j}} \right)  \left( z-z_{{i}} \right) } }+{\frac {1}{ \left( z_{{j}}-z_{{i}} \right)  \left( z-z_{{j}}  \right) }}
\frac { dS } { dz} =\sum _ { i = 1 } ^ n\Pi_{j\neq i}(z-z_j)
 \frac { 1 } {S ( z)}\frac { dS } { dz}=\sum _ { i = 1 } ^ n\Pi_{j\neq i}(z-z_j)/(\Pi_{i=1}^n(z-z_j))=\sum _ { i = 1 } ^ n\frac { 1 } {z - z_i}
